2026-06-19 08:16:24,600 DEBUG Tool call: submit_final_result({'final_result': '## Question: In 2024, who was Nominated to Serve on BBSI\'s (NASDAQ: BBSI) Board of Directors?\n\n### Answer\n\nIn 2024, the following **eight individuals** were nominated to serve on BBSI\'s Board of Directors. All were nominated for re-election at the 2024 Annual Meeting of Stockholders (held on June 3, 2024), as detailed in BBSI\'s Definitive Proxy Statement (DEF 14A) filed with the SEC on April 22, 2024:\n\n| # | Name | Principal Occupation | Director Since |\n|---|------|---------------------|---------------|\n| 1 | **Thomas J. Carley** | Retired Chief Operating Officer of Urth Organic Corporation | 2000 |\n| 2 | **Joseph S. Clabby** | Retired Vice President at Chubb Limited | 2022 |\n| 3 | **Thomas B. Cusick** | Retired Executive Advisor of Columbia Sportswear Company | 2016 |\n| 4 | **Gary E. Kramer** | President and Chief Executive Officer of BBSI | 2020 |\n| 5 | **Anthony Meeker** | Retired Managing Director of Victory Capital Management, Inc. | 1993 |\n| 6 | **Carla A. Moradi** | Board member of BBSI and Patriot Growth Insurance Services, LLC | 2021 |\n| 7 | **Alexandra Morehouse** | Board member of BBSI and Evalueserv, Inc. | 2022 |\n| 8 | **Vincent P. Price** | Advisor to the CEO of Cambia Health Solutions, Inc. | 2017 |\n\nAll eight nominees were already serving as directors and were nominated for election to serve until the 2025 annual meeting of stockholders. The Board of Directors unanimously recommended that stockholders vote **FOR** each nominee.\n\nThe proxy statement noted that a nominee would be elected if they received the affirmative vote of a majority of the total votes cast (i.e., shares voted "for" a nominee must exceed votes cast "against" that nominee).\n\n---\n\n**Sources:**\n\n{\n    "sources": [\n        {\n            "url": "https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/902791/000095017024046428/bbsi-20240422.htm",\n            "name": "Barrett Business Services, Inc. - Definitive Proxy Statement (DEF 14A), Filed April 22, 2024"\n        }\n    ]\n}'})
